http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/BSNL-to-install-BTS/article13991479.ece

Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limited (BSNL) will install temporary Base Transceiver Stations (BTS) at Pulmedu to provide uninterrupted telecommunication facility in the forest tracts during the Makaravilakku festival on the directions of the Kerala High Court.The BTS would be made functional from January 12 to 16. BSNL authorities have been asked to ensure carpet cellular phone coverage in the forest reaches of Vallakakdavu and Kozhikanam on January 14 and 15. He said the telecommunications wing of the police would install repeaters on the Kumily and Pulmedu routes to ensure smooth telecommunications in the last lap of the Makaravilakku festival.The Forest Department will deploy a five-member elephant squad at Pulmedu, besides providing drinking water and snacks to the pilgrims at five points on the forest path leading to Pulmedu.